Q_DESC:
Compare the element of a collection by converting a string into a treeset using 

A. Collection.min() and
B. Collection.max() methods of Collection class

Get the input string array from the user and produce the result as 

A. Collections.min(set)
B. Collections.min(set, String.CASE_INSENSITIVE_ORDER)
C. Collection.max(set)
D. Collections.max(set, String.CASE_INSENSITIVE_ORDER)

Mandatory:

1. Create a String array and the object or instance for String class is coins. 

2. Create a Class Set with String type and the instance for Set class is set with TreeSet  collections of type String
Hint: SetString set=new TreeSetString()

3. Pass the instance of Set class to the following methods in Collections

      a. Collections.min(set)
      b. Collections.min(set,String.CASE_INSENSITIVE_ORDER)
      c. Collections.max(set)
      d. Collections.max(set,String.CASE_INSENSITIVE_ORDER)

 Note: If any one of the above condition is not satisfied, then it will not show 100%
